<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The for loop initializes and updates two variables (i and j) as loop counters: "for (i = idx_first_data, j = 0; i < *length; i++, j++)". MISRA C 2023 Rule 14.2 requires there be only one loop counter and that the third clause modify only that loop counter. Because this loop uses and modifies two counters (i and j) it is not well-formed and thus violates Rule 14.2.
</scenario>

